management of ION; materially changing the present capitalization or dividend policy of ION; making other material changes in IONs business or corporate structure; changing IONs charter, bylaws or instruments corresponding thereto or
other actions which may affect control of ION; causing the ION Common Stock no longer to be quoted on the New York Stock Exchange (the NYSE); causing ION securities to become eligible for termination of registration pursuant to Section
12(g)(4) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (the Exchange Act); or taking any action similar to any of those enumerated above. The actions of Mr. Lapeyre in his capacity as an ION director and chairman of its Board of
Directors may be attributable to Laitram. In such case, Laitram, may be deemed from time to time to consider plans or proposals relating to, or may be a participant, as a shareholder of ION, in the foregoing transactions. 
